  "body": "My use case is rendering an 80 x 80 grid of components and changing state of the parent component via `window.addEventListener` event as per the docs, like so: \n\n```\nComponentDidMount(){\n    window.addEventListener('keydown', this.handleKeyPress);\n  }\n\n  componentWillUnmount(){\n    window.removeEventListener('keydown', this.handleKeyPress);\n  }\n```\n\nIn Chrome 49.0.2623.112, for example, React 14.0.7 is taking ~75ms to re-render and 15.0.01 takes ~270ms.\n\nView console in the examples below to see what I mean. \n\n[14.0.7 example](http://codepen.io/thepeted/pen/ae125e2599234fb05e5bc914db7e300d)\n[15.0.1 example](http://codepen.io/thepeted/pen/f7c85287195fd58622ddc6da1ca0d648)\n",
